            ("Hong Kong salaries tax is computed on:", "香港薪俸稅按以下方式計算：", ["Net chargeable income at progressive rates or net income at standard rate, whichever is lower", "Gross income at a flat rate", "Only basic salary", "Net income minus all expenses"], ["按累進稅率計算的應評稅淨收入或按標準稅率計算的淨收入，以較低者為準", "按統一稅率計算的總收入", "僅基本工資", "淨收入減所有支出"], 0, "Salaries tax = lesser of: 1) progressive rates on net chargeable income (after allowances), 2) standard rate (15%) on net income (before allowances).", "薪俸稅 = 以下較低者：1）按累進稅率計算的應評稅淨收入（扣除免稅額後），2）按標準稅率（15%）計算的淨收入（扣除免稅額前）。"),
            ("Depreciation allowances in Hong Kong for commercial buildings are:", "香港商業樓宇的折舊免稅額為：", ["Initial allowance of 20% and annual allowance of 4%", "100% in the first year", "No depreciation allowances", "25% per year"], ["初期免稅額20%和每年免稅額4%", "第一年100%", "無折舊免稅額", "每年25%"], 0, "Commercial buildings: initial allowance 20% of construction cost, annual allowance 4% of construction cost. Industrial buildings: 20% initial, 4% annual.", "商業樓宇：初期免稅額為建造成本的20%，每年免稅額為建造成本的4%。工業樓宇：初期20%，每年4%。"),
            ("Under Hong Kong tax law, plant and machinery depreciation is claimed via:", "根據香港稅務法例，廠房及機器折舊通過以下方式申索：", ["Initial allowance of 60% and annual allowance at prescribed rates", "Straight-line method only", "No depreciation allowed", "10% flat rate for all assets"], ["初期免稅額60%和按規定稅率的每年免稅額", "僅直線法", "不允許折舊", "所有資產統一10%"], 0, "P&M: 60% initial allowance in first year, then annual allowances (10%-30% reducing balance depending on asset class).", "廠房及機器：第一年60%初期免稅額，然後每年免稅額（按資產類別10%-30%遞減餘額）。"),
            ("A Hong Kong tax loss can be:", "香港稅務虧損可以：", ["Carried forward indefinitely to offset future profits of the same trade", "Carried back to offset prior year profits", "Transferred to group companies", "Used to claim a tax refund"], ["無限期結轉以抵銷同一業務的未來利潤", "結轉以抵銷以前年度利潤", "轉讓給集團公司", "用於申請退稅"], 0, "Hong Kong tax losses can be carried forward indefinitely to offset future profits from the same trade, profession, or business. No group relief or carry-back.", "香港稅務虧損可無限期結轉以抵銷同一行業、專業或業務的未來利潤。無集團稅務寬免或結轉回撥。"),
            ("The Inland Revenue Department (IRD) assesses tax based on:", "稅務局根據以下評稅：", ["The previous year's basis period (preceding year basis)", "The current year's estimated profits", "The average of the last 3 years", "Cash received during the year"], ["上一年度的評稅基期（上年度基礎）", "本年度預計利潤", "過去3年的平均值", "年內收到的現金"], 0, "Hong Kong uses the preceding year basis: tax for a year of assessment is based on the profits of the year ending in that assessment year.", "香港採用上年度基礎：某一評稅年度的稅項基於在該評稅年度內結束的年度利潤。"),
            ("Stamp duty in Hong Kong is payable on:", "香港印花稅須繳付於：", ["Stock transfers, property transfers, and leases", "Only property purchases", "Only share transfers", "Income from employment"], ["股票轉讓、物業轉讓和租約", "僅物業購買", "僅股份轉讓", "就業收入"], 0, "Hong Kong stamp duty applies to: stock transfers (0.13% each side), property transfers (up to 15%), and leases (0.25-1% of rental value).", "香港印花稅適用於：股票轉讓（每方0.13%）、物業轉讓（最高15%）和租約（租金價值的0.25%-1%）。"),
            ("Double taxation agreements (DTAs) signed by Hong Kong primarily aim to:", "香港簽訂的雙重徵稅協定主要旨在：", ["Prevent double taxation and provide certainty on tax treatment", "Increase tax rates", "Eliminate all taxes for foreign companies", "Transfer taxing rights to Hong Kong only"], ["防止雙重徵稅並為稅務處理提供確定性", "提高稅率", "取消外國公司的所有稅項", "僅將徵稅權轉移給香港"], 0, "DTAs allocate taxing rights between jurisdictions, provide reduced withholding tax rates, and offer mechanisms for resolving tax disputes to prevent double taxation.", "DTAs在稅收管轄區之間分配徵稅權、提供較低預扣稅率，並提供解決稅務爭議的機制以防止雙重徵稅。"),
            ("Anti-avoidance provisions under Hong Kong's Inland Revenue Ordinance allow the IRD to:", "香港《稅務條例》中的反避稅條款允許稅務局：", ["Recompute profits to counteract tax avoidance schemes", "Only issue warnings", "Only audit large companies", "Increase tax rates arbitrarily"], ["重新計算利潤以抵消避稅計劃", "僅發出警告", "僅審計大公司", "任意提高稅率"], 0, "Section 61 allows IRD to disregard/modify transactions that are artificial, fictitious, or designed to avoid tax. Section 61A targets transactions with tax avoidance as the dominant purpose.", "第61條允許稅務局無視/修改人為、虛構或旨在避稅的交易。第61A條針對以避稅為主要目的的交易。"),
