            ("An initial public offering (IPO) involves:", "首次公開招股涉及：", ["Offering shares to the public for the first time through a prospectus", "Selling the entire company", "Borrowing from the public", "Issuing bonds"], ["通過招股章程首次向公眾發售股份", "出售整個公司", "向公眾借款", "發行債券"], 0, "IPO = first public offering of shares. Process: appoint underwriters, file prospectus with regulator, roadshow, price allocation, listing on stock exchange.", "IPO = 首次公開發售股份。流程：委任保薦人、向監管機構提交招股章程、路演、定價分配、在證券交易所上市。"),
            ("The pecking order theory of capital structure suggests firms prefer:", "資本結構的優序融資理論認為公司偏好：", ["Internal financing first, then debt, then equity", "Equity first, then debt", "Debt first, then equity", "Equal amounts of debt and equity"], ["先內部融資，然後債務，然後股權", "先股權，然後債務", "先債務，然後股權", "等量的債務和股權"], 0, "Pecking order (Myers & Majluf): firms prefer internal funds → debt → equity, due to information asymmetry costs and adverse selection in external financing.", "優序融資（Myers和Majluf）：由於信息不對稱成本和外部融資中的逆向選擇，公司偏好內部資金→債務→股權。"),
            ("Mergers and acquisitions (M&A) synergies include:", "合併和收購的協同效應包括：", ["Revenue synergies, cost synergies, and financial synergies", "Only cost reductions", "Only revenue increases", "Only tax benefits"], ["收入協同效應、成本協同效應和財務協同效應", "僅成本削減", "僅收入增加", "僅稅務優惠"], 0, "M&A synergies: revenue (cross-selling, market access), cost (economies of scale, eliminating duplicates), financial (lower WACC, tax benefits, diversification).", "M&A協同效應：收入（交叉銷售、市場准入）、成本（規模經濟、消除重複）、財務（降低WACC、稅務優惠、多元化）。"),
